Author: Cryptoon#3362
Content: Yeah, that's what I also say to people that don't know what to do with their lives.

Author: Cryptoon#3362
Content: If you are young and still don't have any solid commitments in real life such as a house, wife, children etc, it's still relatively easy to pivot into a new venture

Author: Cryptoon#3362
Content: By solid commitments I mean stuff that costs a lot of money to maintain. Such as debt payments etc.

Author: Cryptoon#3362
Content: Because once you have those you need a steady stream of income to support those and pivoting to other industries/ventures/learning new skills becomes harder to do
